# NirmiqLearn OS — Cursor Rules

## Project Identity
Local-first AI learning OS. Next.js 16 · TypeScript · Tailwind CSS 4 · SQLite + Drizzle · Zod · Zustand.
Tagline: "Build with AI, but learn like a real engineer."

## Before Coding
- Read docs/CONTEXT.md first.
- Read docs/GRAPHIFY_MAP.md to find relevant files. Do not scan the whole repo.
- Read the specific doc for the task (TRD for technical, UI_UX for UI, DEBUGGING for bugs).

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode always.
- Small focused components. No files over ~200 lines.
- Zod for all validation at boundaries.
- Service functions return `{ ok: true; data: T } | { ok: false; error: string }`.
- No premature abstractions. Three similar lines > a helper no one asked for.
- No comments unless explaining a non-obvious WHY.

## Architecture Rules
- Persistent data → SQLite via Drizzle. Never in Zustand.
- Zustand only for: selectedWorkspaceId, sidebarCollapsed, theme, UI filters.
- App Router server components for data fetching. Server Actions for mutations.
- API routes only if server actions are insufficient.

## UI Rules
- Dark academic theme. Background: near-black (#0a0c10). Accent: cyan-400/500.
- Every page must show: "What should the user do next?"
- Empty states must guide action, never just say "Nothing here."
- Badges for: workspace type (project/dsa/exam/topic), confidence (red/yellow/green).
- shadcn/ui components only. No raw HTML inputs.

## After Every Change
Run: `npm run lint` → `npm run typecheck` → `npm run build`
Commit with conventional type: feat / fix / docs / style / refactor / chore / db

## Never
- Commit .env, *.db, node_modules, secrets.
- Push unless user asks.
- Use generic AI chatbot UI patterns.
- Store learning data in Zustand.
- Build beyond the current phase scope.
